    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>MAXTOR BUYING QUANTUM DISK</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Andrew Ross Sorkin</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Sorkin, Andrew Ross</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Maxtor, maker of lowpriced hard disk drives, agrees to acquire Quantum's hard disk drive group for about $1.3 billion in stock, creating world's largest computer hard drive manufacturer; graph (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The maker of lowpriced hard disk drives Maxtor said yesterday that it had agreed to acquire Quantum's hard disk drive group for about $1.3 billion in stock, creating the world's largest computer hard drive manufacturer. Maxtor will exchange 1.52 of its shares for each share of Quantum HDD. Shares of Maxtor fell 4 percent, to $9.38 yesterday, while Quantum jumped 38 percent, to $13.25.</p>
        <p>Andrew Ross Sorkin</p>
      </block>
